Package org.team1540.rooster.testers.motor

Class SimpleControllersTester

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.SendableBase
      • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
        • org.team1540.rooster.testers.motor.SimpleControllersTester
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sendable, AutoCloseable
    public class SimpleControllersTester
extends Command
implements Sendable
    A simple command for testing a series of IMotorControllers. Simply add the controllers, specify control bindings or use the defaults, and you're ready! Select the motor in the SmartDashboard or move next/previous with buttons and control the percent output of the motor with a joystick axis.

      • SimpleControllersTester

        public SimpleControllersTester​(com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.IMotorController... controllers)
        Construct a new instance with the default bindings on Joystick 0. On an Xbox controller, the right thumbstick y-axis controls ControlMode.PERCENT_OUTPUT, the A button goes to the next IMotorController, and the B button goes to the previous IMotorController.
        Parameters:
        controllers - The IMotorControllers to test.
